{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.32",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 32,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 32",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 32 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:1",
      "text": "So these three men ceased to answer Job, because he was righteous in his own eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:2",
      "text": "Then was kindled the wrath of Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite, of the kindred of Ram: against Job was his wrath kindled, because he justified himself rather than God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:3",
      "text": "Also against his three friends was his wrath kindled, because they had found no answer, and yet had condemned Job.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:4",
      "text": "Now Elihu had waited till Job had spoken, because they were elder than he.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:5",
      "text": "When Elihu saw that there was no answer in the mouth of these three men, then his wrath was kindled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:6",
      "text": "And Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite answered and said, I am young, and ye are very old; wherefore I was afraid, and durst not shew you mine opinion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:7",
      "text": "I said, Days should speak, and multitude of years should teach wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:8",
      "text": "But there is a spirit in man: and the inspiration of the Almighty giveth them understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:9",
      "text": "Great men are not always wise: neither do the aged understand judgment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:10",
      "text": "Therefore I said, Hearken to me; I also will shew mine opinion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:11",
      "text": "Behold, I waited for your words; I gave ear to your reasons, whilst ye searched out what to say.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:12",
      "text": "Yea, I attended unto you, and, behold, there was none of you that convinced Job, or that answered his words:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:13",
      "text": "Lest ye should say, We have found out wisdom: God thrusteth him down, not man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:14",
      "text": "Now he hath not directed his words against me: neither will I answer him with your speeches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:15",
      "text": "They were amazed, they answered no more: they left off speaking.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:16",
      "text": "When I had waited, (for they spake not, but stood still, and answered no more;)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:17",
      "text": "I said, I will answer also my part, I also will shew mine opinion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:18",
      "text": "For I am full of matter, the spirit within me constraineth me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:19",
      "text": "Behold, my belly is as wine which hath no vent; it is ready to burst like new bottles.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:20",
      "text": "I will speak, that I may be refreshed: I will open my lips and answer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:21",
      "text": "Let me not, I pray you, accept any man’s person, neither let me give flattering titles unto man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.32.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 32:22",
      "text": "For I know not to give flattering titles; in so doing my maker would soon take me away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
